body.description: Equip your kitchen for less with these essential knives.The 2-piece utility set features two key knives in the kitchen: the serrated utility knife and the paring knife. The compact serrated utility knife is for cutting foods with a hard exterior and soft interior, like tomatoes, salami, and bagel. The paring knife is ideal for smaller scale jobs like peeling vegetables and segmenting fruit.Since 1895, Henckels has been making high quality knives at an exceptional value. Dynamic knives can tackle every kitchen task. Fabricated from high-quality stainless steel, single-piece, precision-stamped Dynamic knives are lightweight without sacrificing strength and durability. The professional, satin-polished, fine-edge blades boast superior sharpness—they are finely honed for long-lasting precision.The ergonomic, traditional triple-rivet handles are comfortable to grip for fatigue-free cutting. Easy to use, the dishwasher-safe Dynamic knives are also easy to maintain.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent quality knife set
reviews.reviewText: These knives far exceeded my expectations. The quality was great especially considering how reasonably priced they were. I haven’t had a chance to use them yet but they look well made and sharp and hopefully will last a long time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Henkel knife set
reviews.reviewText: I ordered a Henkel pairing knife from another retailer and the metal was very thin, so I was apprehensive about ordering these. But these knives are great and made from quality materials. I may just order another set at this great price!!$

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Careful...these are sharp.
reviews.reviewText: First thing I did when trying out the searated knife was to slice my thumb open. I feel like the knives are made to last but I feel like they need better ergonomics in the handle so you can get a better grip on the knife. I kept fumbling while cutting an onion and found that the knife had slipped in my hand and the sharp edge was facing up. This happened several times. For some reason I just can't keep a good grip on the knives. I still like them and hope I will get more savy using them. They are both a great size and make a nice set.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best knives I owned in years
reviews.reviewText: Cut superbly, handle nicely. I expect them to last 15-20 years. I would buy them again (but probably won't need to).
